snippet.title: Amber Liu Is Proud To Be An Androgynous Asian-American Artist (Ep. 3) | Homecoming
snippet.description:
At the age of 16, Amber Liu moved from Los Angeles to Seoul to train with one of South Korea’s top entertainment companies. In 2009, Liu debuted with f(x), a K-pop girl group known for the members’ distinct personas. Liu’s androgyny and charisma made her a star in Korea. Now, ten years later, the Taiwanese-American artist is back in the U.S. looking to relaunch her pop career Stateside — and she’s finally doing it on her own terms.
